"&#xa0;\nSupplementary written evidence submitted by the Electoral Commission (DWB 17)&#xa0;\nReferendum on the law-making powers of the National Assembly for Wales (\nhttp://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0019/118603/Wales-ref-report-FINAL-web-mail.pdf\n)\nTurnout: 36% (Page three)\nCost: £5.89 million (Page 58)\n&#xa0;\nReferendum on the Parliamentary Voting System\nTurnout: 42% (\nhttp://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0019/141328/Final-PVS-report.pdf\n Page four) *\nCost: £75 million (\nhttp://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0009/153000/Costs-of-UK-May-2011-UKPVS-referendum.pdf\n)\n&#xa0;\n*This turnout figure is UK-wide but given that this referendum was combined with the elections to the National Assembly for Wales, where turnout was 41.8%, we can estimate that 42% is an accurate turnout figure for Wales\n&#xa0;\n22 January 2014\n&#xa0;\n"